org.modelio.api.module.propertiesPage

Interface IModulePropertyPage

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractModulePropertyPage

    public interface IModulePropertyPage
    Interface defining a module's property view.

    The main methods are update(List, IModulePropertyTable) and {changeProperty(List, int, String)}, respectively used to display the property page's content, and to update the a field's value.

    All modules should extend AbstractModulePropertyPage instead of implementing this interface.

      • update

        void update(List<MObject> elements,
          IModulePropertyTable table)
        This method is called to provide the properties that will populate the module properties view.

        Overwrite this method in the class generated by MDA Designer to provide properties.

        By default, nothing is done when the table should be updated.

        Parameters:
        elements - the elements to load the properties from.
        table - the property page's data model.

      • changeProperty

        void changeProperty(List<MObject> elements,
                  int row,
                  String value)
        This method is called when the user modify the value of a property.

        Overwrite this method to modify the model when the user modify a value.

        By default, nothing is done when a property is changed.

        Parameters:
        elements - the elements to change the properties into.
        row - the line of the modified property.
        value - the value set in the property.
